135.1	Altruism	Altruism	Altruism is a concern for the welfare of others. It is a traditional virtue in many cultures, and a core aspect of various religious traditions, though the concept of 'others' toward whom concern should be directed can vary among cultures and religions. Altruism is the opposite of selfishness.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Belisaire_demandant_l%27aumone_Jacques-Louis_David.jpg/325px-Belisaire_demandant_l%27aumone_Jacques-Louis_David.jpg
